Hi,

I did try once and successfully built ocamlbrowser and the Tk-based
applications found in the examples directory.  These applications work but
are quite unstable: GUI components quivering all the time on the windows,
frequent crashes, and bad influence to the Finder application.

Attached to this message is the configure script that I used for Tcl/Tk Aqua
installation.

You might be interested in Trevor Jim's message as of 2002/11/13 titled
"Aqua (non-X) labltk on Mac OS 10".

If you get better results I am happy to hear.

Ken Wakita

